result.name: West Villa Restaurant

reviews.text: Chinese seafood restaurant. Reasonable prices for quality cooking. Long time customers usually. Better make reservations, always fully booked at dinner.

This is one of my favorite Cantonese dim-sum restaurants in Hong Kong. The place is clean and comfortable. Quality of the food is very good and everything is scrumptious. Apart from the dim-sum, their fried rice and noodles are also very tasty. I recommend the yin-yang rice particularly.
Great Food n Din Sum here. Avg. waiting time is 30-45 mins

Good food, reasonable price. Very stable quality. Unfortunately very difficult to get a table on weekend dinners. I especially like the hot pot veggie, sizzling hot and very soothing. The red bean soup dessert is great too.
A very busy Dim Sum Restaurant that offers discount to customers who settle their bills before 12:30pm (Mon - Sat) or before 12 noon (Sun and holidays). Food is tasty and service is friendly.

result.name: 西苑酒家

reviews.text:
叉燒不錯👍🏼
爵士湯好味👍🏼一陣間就賣晒。
太古城裏面其中一間較多人嘅酒樓。早/午茶方面，平日人流較少，周末就比較多人，waiting time ~ 45 mins to 1 hour。點心同炒粉飯麵係幾好食，性價比幾高。晚飯小菜類都OK，大哥叉燒值得一試。
